1. PROBLEM STATEMENT
================================================================================

The current simulation/ directory models the V1 belt-pusher architecture from
archive2/v1_belt_pusher/. This design used:
- Timing-based sorting with 3 solenoid pushers on belt
- Stepper escapement cam for brick release
- Sensing on moving belt (chute exit sensor)
- Critical timing dependencies (belt position calculated for pusher fire)

The V6 chamber-drop architecture (current design) is fundamentally different:
- Static isolation chamber with trapdoor mechanism
- Token-based single-brick constraint (physically enforced geometry)
- Static sensing (belt OFF, brick seated against stop wall)
- Pre-committed routing via 4-position chute selector disc
- Class 3 lever actuated by solenoid for gravity drop
- Zero timing dependencies (correctness enforced by geometry and state)

GOAL: Replace V1 simulation with V6 simulation that accurately models the new
      architecture for timing validation, thermal prediction, and speed tuning.


