================================================================================
3. V6 ARCHITECTURE SUMMARY
================================================================================

STATE MACHINE FLOW:
IDLE -> FEED -> APPROACH -> SEATED -> SENSING -> INDEXED -> RELEASED -> CONFIRM -> RESET -> IDLE
                                                                                    |
                                                                             COMPLETE (after brick 24)
                                                      ERROR_HALT from any state on fault

KEY STATE PHASES TO MODEL:
1. FEED: Belt on, brick travels from entry beam to stop switch (FEED_TIMEOUT_MS)
2. APPROACH: Entry beam triggered, brick pushed to stop wall (APPROACH_TIMEOUT_MS)
3. SEATED: Stop switch active, belt OFF, settle delay (SETTLE_MS)
4. SENSING: Read size beams, accumulate color samples (COLOR_TIMEOUT_MS, COLOR_SAMPLE_COUNT)
5. INDEXED: Stepper rotates disc to target bin (ramp profile, StallGuard monitor)
6. RELEASED: Solenoid fires, lever sweeps, platform drops, brick falls (SOLENOID_ON_MS + FALL_SETTLE_MS)
7. CONFIRM: Monitor bin beam for arrival (BIN_CONFIRM_TIMEOUT_MS)
8. RESET: Platform return, token restore, brick_count++

BIN ASSIGNMENTS:
- Bin 1 (NW, 315deg): 2x2 red, count 6
- Bin 2 (NE, 45deg): 2x2 blue, count 6
- Bin 3 (SE, 135deg): 2x3 blue, count 8
- Bin 4 (SW DEFAULT, 225deg): 2x3 red, count 4

SENSING:
- Size: Dual IR break-beams at X=5mm and X=21mm, 16mm spacing
  Both LOW = 2x3, else = 2x2
- Color: TCS34725 through 12mm x 12mm window with black shroud
  R/(R+G+B) ratio averaged over COLOR_SAMPLE_COUNT samples


