6. IMPLEMENTATION NOTES
================================================================================

WHAT THE V6 SIMULATION SHOULD MODEL:
- Discrete event timing for each state transition
- Stepper indexing time based on sps, acceleration, distance
- Solenoid thermal accumulation and cooldown
- Stepper thermal accumulation from continuous motion
- Bin capacity and overflow detection
- Multi-run thermal effects with inter-run gap cooling
- CSV replay from real firmware logs

WHAT THE V6 SIMULATION SHOULD NOT MODEL:
- Fine-grained physics (falling brick trajectory, lever dynamics, spring forces)
- Sensor noise or calibration drift
- Mechanical wear or part tolerance
- Electrical transients or power supply sag

REFERENCE THE OLD SIMULATION FOR:
- Thermal model structure (heat accumulation, exponential decay, misfire probability)
- Build system approach (esbuild bundling, inline CSS/JS into single HTML)
- UI control generation from SECTIONS array
- Canvas animation loop structure
- CSV replay parser structure

SKIP FROM OLD SIMULATION:
- All belt-pusher-specific routing logic (timing-based, V6 is state-based)
- Plow fire timing calculations
- Belt position tracking for pusher activation

OLD SIMULATION LOCATION:
- Will be archived to: archive2/v1_belt_pusher_simulation/
- Reference thermal.js for heat model
- Reference build.sh for bundle process
- Reference src/ structure for module organization


