9. COMMIT STRATEGY
================================================================================

GUIDELINES:
- One commit per completed todo (modular, surgical changes)
- Follow COMMIT_GUIDE.log format (action-oriented subjects, no function names)
- Subject line: short, action-oriented, product/behavior framing
- Optional body: why the change was needed, user impact
- No file paths, function names, or variable names in subject
- No tooling or agent references
- No "Co-authored-by" trailers
- Keep wording concise, plain, ASCII-only

GOOD EXAMPLES FOR THIS PROJECT:
- "add V6 state machine discrete event model"
- "add chute selector disc rendering with rotation"
- "add thermal accumulation for stepper and solenoid"
- "add CSV replay parser for firmware logs"
- "add parameter validation warnings"

BAD EXAMPLES:
- "update src/simulation.js to add computeSimulation()"
- "fix bug in thermal model"
- "WIP simulation changes"
- "agent-generated simulation overhaul"


